			<h1 class="notsobig">What's the difference between BC Bike RACE and BC Bike RIDE?</h1>
			<p>At our RACE things are a bit more structured.  You are being timed on a set course that everyone follows and drives the ambitious goal of becoming an official BC Bike Race Finisher. In any race, you typically would not 'session' a feature or re-ride a trail that you really liked - time is of the essence and you must keep going!     But at BC BIKE RIDE, you will have that freedom. <span class="bolder">It's about exploration on your own terms and about picking your own adventure each day</span>.   We get you there and show you the way, but YOU get to choose how, what, and how much you want to ride.   There will be recommended routes, detailed maps, local guides, and shuttles to get to the trails.    XC, Epic, DH,  Enduro, freeride, dirt jumping - in BC, we just call it all 'mountain biking'.  <span class="bolder">However you define your individual riding style, you will enjoy this adventure on your terms</span>.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<a name="anchorPanel7"></a>
	<section class="fullbleed homePanel7">
		<div class="dimmer"></div>
		<div class="contentWrap">
			<p>The end of your journey will be complete with a traditional salmon banquet at the historic <span class="italic bolder"><a href="http://www.cassiarcannery.com/" target="_blank">Cassiar Cannery</a></span>, where history and nature meet by the estuary of the mighty Skeena River within the Great Bear Rainforest Conservancy.<br><br>   
				After you have ridden your ass off for 7 days with your new long-lost friends, relax and enjoy available nature tours including: whale watching, jet boat tours, or deep sea fishing that will be organized for you.   The <span class="italic bolder"><a href="http://www.cassiarcannery.com/" target="_blank">Cassiar Cannery</a></span>, one of the "Top 10 Most Unique Places to Overnight in British Columbia", is your gateway to adventure on the North Coast and world famous <span class="bolder">Haida Gwaii</span>.</p>
		</div>
	</section>	
	
	<a name="anchorPanel13"></a>
	<section class="fullbleed homePanel13">
		<div class="dimmer"></div>
		<div class="contentWrap">
			<h1>Package Details</h1>
			<p class="smaller" style="margin-top: 1rem;">* Details Subject To Change</p>
			<div class="contentCol">
				<h3>Riding</h3>
				<p>7-days of intermediate to advanced all-mountain singletrack riding</p> 
				<p>14 distinct trail networks to explore</p>
				<p>7-8 hours of riding available daily</p>
				<p>The best access to each trail network provided daily and may include:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Shuttles</li>
					<li>Guided rides</li>
					<li>Climbing and descending (all-mountain riding)</li>
					<li>Detailed maps, signage, and local trail ambassadors </li>
				</ul>
				<div style="clear:both;"></div>

				<h3>Meals</h3>
				<p>Three gourmet meals a day, including a packed lunch, prepared by local caterers. <br>Starting with lunch on August 6 and ending with breakfast on August 13</p>
				<p>A traditional West Coast final banquet featuring fresh caught local sockeye salmon hosted by the historic Cassiar Cannery</p>
				<div style="clear:both;"></div>
				<h3>Swag</h3>
				<p>Custom BC Bike Race Bag</p>
				<p>Custom BC Bike Ride T-shirt</p>
				<p>Further BC Bike Ride Swag TBA</p>
			</div>
			<div class="contentCol">
				<h3>Basecamp</h3>
				<p>Roomy 4-person sized tents for double occupancy</p>
				<p>Solo tent upgrades available </p>
				<p>On-site mobile washrooms and hot shower trucks</p>
				<p>On-site mechanical support</p>
				<p>On-site medical support</p>
				<p>Campfire every night</p>
				<p>Varied nightly entertainment </p>
				<p>Emersion into local culture and presentations on local history</p>
				<div style="clear:both;"></div>
				<h3>Beer</h3>
				<p>Unlimited local craft beer </p>
				<div style="clear:both;"></div>
				<h3>Travel</h3>
				<p>A total of 3000 kilometres traveled through the vast and scenic northern British Columbia by plane, coach bus, train, and bike:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Two flights; Vancouver International Airport (YVR) to Northern British Columbia and return</li>
					<li>A private train car between Smithers and Terrace</li>
					<li>Coach buses with washrooms and wifi (where available) will transport riders between basecamps</li>
					<li>Average bus ride times are 2-2.5 hours</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			
			<div style="clear: both;"></div>
			<h1>$3999.00 CAD/Per Person</h1>
			<p>Join the BCBR crew and other like-minded mountain bikers on the maiden voyage of the BC BIKE RIDE in Northern BC - coming August 5 - 13, 2017. Your ultimate road trip experience awaits!  We only have 100 spots available for our inaugural tour and it will be a very special event. This new venture is the result of many years of dreaming and planning, so we are excited to finally launch it and start our next decade of adventure tourism in BC. Come make your own history with us this summer.</p>
		</div>
	</section>	
	
